WEBVTT

01:06.801 --> 01:11.539
The practice of Cursive Writing
in the handwriting system

01:11.573 --> 01:13.675
known as the Palmer Method

01:13.708 --> 01:15.543
will be one of the most
important things

01:15.577 --> 01:17.745
you will ever learn.

01:17.779 --> 01:21.516
In basic loop practice,
we embody a balance

01:21.549 --> 01:26.353
between control and relaxation.

01:26.386 --> 01:30.390
Success in the execution
of Palmer loops

01:30.424 --> 01:35.697
demands that you locate
the beat of your inner drummer.

01:35.730 --> 01:40.233
The heartbeat that guides
your handwriting.

01:49.443 --> 01:53.246
Silence!

01:56.383 --> 01:59.621
It's this class called
Art Without Boundaries.

01:59.654 --> 02:01.923
It's where people that
are differently-abled

02:01.956 --> 02:04.291
create together.

02:04.324 --> 02:06.193
Mm-hmm.

02:06.226 --> 02:08.495
I want to photograph folks
with verbal challenges

02:08.529 --> 02:11.398
as they make art.

02:11.431 --> 02:14.936
As Valedictorian, you know,
you got a real opportunity here.

02:14.969 --> 02:17.404
You know, your thesis is going
to be heavily scrutinized.

02:17.437 --> 02:20.374
I'm just not sure taking
pictures is really enough.

02:20.407 --> 02:23.477
And for the literary connection
to your class

02:23.511 --> 02:27.180
well, maybe we can use
Ginsberg's American Sentences?

02:27.214 --> 02:29.483
From class?

02:29.517 --> 02:34.388
And I was hoping
you'd be my advisor.

02:34.421 --> 02:38.458
Ahh.

02:38.492 --> 02:41.294
My grandmother had Alzheimer's.

02:41.328 --> 02:44.331
We used to be really close
before she got sick.

02:44.364 --> 02:48.603
Towards the end,
she didn't know any of us.

02:48.636 --> 02:53.373
I'm just sorry I didn't find out
more about her.

02:57.812 --> 03:03.751
"Who tells the stories of people
who have limited or no language?

03:03.785 --> 03:09.724
Is there a way to help such
people tell their own stories?"

03:16.329 --> 03:17.875
Up, down, and around.
Up, down, and around.

03:17.899 --> 03:20.668
Palmer Method Cursive Loop
practice has been shown

03:20.702 --> 03:22.770
to light up little-used

03:22.804 --> 03:26.641
or even failing connections
in the brain.

03:26.674 --> 03:29.010
Up, down, and around.

03:29.043 --> 03:31.311
Up, down, and around.

03:31.344 --> 03:33.514
Up, down, and around.

03:33.548 --> 03:35.583
Up, down, and around.

03:35.616 --> 03:37.752
Up, down, and around.

03:37.785 --> 03:39.854
Up, down, and around.

03:39.887 --> 03:43.290
Up, down, and around.

03:43.323 --> 03:46.326
Bravo.

03:46.359 --> 03:52.499
Please, she often thinks she's
back teaching at our school.

03:52.533 --> 03:56.804
If people can just let her
have that story.

04:04.377 --> 04:07.882
Goodbye, Sister.

04:07.915 --> 04:10.585
Ciao.

04:12.520 --> 04:14.454
Goodbye.

04:14.488 --> 04:15.957
God bless.

04:15.990 --> 04:17.658
We will see you again soon.

