This is your new room, Giorgia.

04:40.114 --> 04:45.318
See? All your things are here.

04:45.352 --> 04:46.687
No.

04:46.721 --> 04:48.756
Look, look, look.

04:48.790 --> 04:50.825
Your pillow is there.

04:50.858 --> 04:53.594
See?

05:35.970 --> 05:38.706
Charles, stop avoiding me.

05:38.739 --> 05:42.577
Call me back.

05:42.610 --> 05:46.379
We need to talk about Cody,
Charles.

05:46.413 --> 05:52.854
Charles, just call me back.

06:28.823 --> 06:31.859
Ta-da.

06:31.893 --> 06:34.028
Do you like my dress?

06:34.061 --> 06:35.596
It's new.

06:35.630 --> 06:38.933
It's from
Frederick and Nelson's.

06:38.966 --> 06:43.170
Your father bought it
especially.

06:43.204 --> 06:45.006
When is Catherine coming?

06:45.039 --> 06:47.875
Soon.

07:02.823 --> 07:06.594
God, would you look at
all those kids.

07:06.627 --> 07:09.462
Pew, pew, pew.

07:09.496 --> 07:13.134
Oh honey,
you forgot your button.

07:15.536 --> 07:18.506
Why don't we have more kids?

07:18.539 --> 07:20.074
Phrase it properly, Charles.

07:20.107 --> 07:22.009
I think what you mean to say is,

07:22.043 --> 07:27.114
Why don't you and Dad
have more children?

07:27.148 --> 07:30.818
Well, why don't you?

07:30.851 --> 07:35.488
Because God knew I could only
be a good mother to one child.

07:35.523 --> 07:38.225
Like Mary.

07:45.833 --> 07:48.069
Mr. and Mrs. Marlow,

07:48.102 --> 07:50.638
I know this may not be
what you want to hear,

07:50.671 --> 07:53.507
but I'm hoping
you're open to the idea.

07:53.541 --> 07:56.277
I believe we should try
medication.

07:56.310 --> 07:59.213
Selective Serotonin
Reuptake Inhibitors

07:59.246 --> 08:01.615
have proven efficacious

08:01.649 --> 08:05.186
for some children with Cody's...

08:05.219 --> 08:06.988
behaviors.

08:07.021 --> 08:09.156
Now, you would have to
take extensive notes

08:09.190 --> 08:11.826
on how Cody's mood might shift.

08:11.859 --> 08:14.295
But we can start
as early as this week.

08:14.328 --> 08:17.598
Aspergillus, Cladosporium,

08:17.631 --> 08:23.037
Stachybotrys, Penicillin,
are most likely.

08:23.070 --> 08:25.606
Hopefully we're just dealing
with standard

08:25.639 --> 08:27.241
run of the mill black mold.

08:27.274 --> 08:29.143
In which case,
the protocols are clear,

08:29.176 --> 08:31.746
and have proven to be
very effective.

08:31.779 --> 08:35.683
I don't know why we didn't think
about this before.

08:35.716 --> 08:37.118
Black mold.

08:37.151 --> 08:40.654
Yes, in the crawlspace.

08:40.688 --> 08:43.758
I mean, we're probably all sick

08:43.791 --> 08:46.027
and don't even know about it,
right?

08:46.060 --> 08:48.729
That's quite possible,
I'm sorry to say.

08:48.763 --> 08:50.698
And of course,
a child's immune system...

08:50.731 --> 08:53.134
Is so much more vulnerable.

08:53.167 --> 08:55.669
Precisely.

08:55.703 --> 08:58.672
Is he toilet-trained?

09:04.311 --> 09:07.014
He can write his own name.

09:07.048 --> 09:11.652
Well, some recent studies
have linked immune responses

09:11.685 --> 09:15.189
to Sick Building Syndrome.

09:15.222 --> 09:21.762
And to the Autism Spectrum,
actually.

09:21.796 --> 09:24.632
Umm...

09:26.801 --> 09:31.205
No... No one has mentioned
Autism before.

09:31.238 --> 09:35.643
We'll do whatever it takes
to make it better.

09:35.676 --> 09:41.282
Is he tantrumming
more than usual?

09:41.315 --> 09:45.152
You could say that.

09:45.186 --> 09:48.355
And he has lost his words?

09:51.392 --> 09:54.095
Alison.

09:56.063 --> 10:01.402
I believe we are dealing
with Sick Building Syndrome.

10:01.435 --> 10:05.339
As caused by
biological contaminants.

10:05.372 --> 10:07.241
We can't move.

10:07.274 --> 10:09.743
I mean, that's the only home
that Cody has ever known.

10:09.777 --> 10:12.379
And he loves the trees,
he loves...

10:12.413 --> 10:16.617
That is of course your decision.

10:55.122 --> 11:00.060
We are going to bind
our arms to our rulers.

11:00.094 --> 11:06.200
The cloths are to be wrapped
and tied in three locations.

11:06.233 --> 11:08.936
First, around the palm
of the hand,

11:08.969 --> 11:11.438
between the thumb
and forefinger.

11:11.472 --> 11:14.875
Then, around the wrist.

11:14.909 --> 11:18.112
And finally, around the forearm
just below the elbow.

11:18.145 --> 11:19.880
Any questions?

11:19.914 --> 11:22.082
Okay, let's get this done.

11:22.116 --> 11:25.252
Mm, ugh.

11:34.529 --> 11:38.432
Please keep your talking
to a minimum.

11:38.465 --> 11:41.135
Please sit up straight.

11:41.168 --> 11:43.971
Position yourself properly.

11:44.004 --> 11:45.507
Take up your pencils, and begin

11:45.540 --> 11:51.745
your one-minute timed
loop practice, now.

11:56.518 --> 11:59.119
Come on, Dana, you can do this.

11:59.153 --> 12:01.889
Take your pencil.

12:01.922 --> 12:04.925
Come on.

12:17.338 --> 12:18.405
Five.

12:18.439 --> 12:19.473
Four.

12:19.507 --> 12:20.841
Three.

12:20.874 --> 12:21.909
Two.

12:21.942 --> 12:24.345
One.

12:24.378 --> 12:26.380
Dana McGucken, that's enough!

12:26.413 --> 12:29.950
Calm down!

12:29.984 --> 12:32.953
Take it off him.

12:38.526 --> 12:40.528
I'm sorry, Dana.

12:40.562 --> 12:43.264
I'm very sorry.

12:43.297 --> 12:45.199
It's all right,

12:45.232 --> 12:48.902
it's all right.

12:48.936 --> 12:51.405
You won't have to do that again.

13:01.282 --> 13:04.485
Mrs. Braxton,
your nose is bleeding.

13:12.893 --> 13:16.497
Let us continue.

13:16.531 --> 13:23.070
Please begin your one-minute
bed spring oval practice, now.

13:44.058 --> 13:47.394
Good morning, Cody.

13:51.432 --> 13:55.235
Oh boy, a new day.

13:55.269 --> 14:00.374
A new chance for Cody
to earn lots of stickers.

14:00.407 --> 14:04.311
Okay now, Cody, time to get up.

