psychological terms

19:55.530 --> 19:59.801
this would be known as denial.

20:06.674 --> 20:09.376
He's lost all his words.

20:13.614 --> 20:17.384
What do you think
is wrong with him?

20:17.417 --> 20:19.020
There his is.

20:19.053 --> 20:21.421
There's my snuggle bunny.

20:21.455 --> 20:22.757
Sweetheart!

20:22.790 --> 20:25.526
Hello, darling.

20:25.560 --> 20:28.796
Eskimo kiss.

20:28.830 --> 20:33.333
Horse kiss.

20:33.366 --> 20:38.973
Butterfly kiss.

20:39.006 --> 20:40.775
What I believe,
Charles, doesn't matter.

20:40.808 --> 20:42.577
Not in the long run.

20:42.610 --> 20:47.314
It's what you and Alison
believe that's important.

20:50.685 --> 20:52.352
Hi, you've reached Charles.

20:52.385 --> 20:56.490
Leave a message.

20:56.524 --> 20:57.925
Charles, I know you're there.

20:57.959 --> 21:00.561
It's a school night.

21:00.595 --> 21:03.296
Pick up.

21:03.330 --> 21:05.566
Pick up, Charles.

21:15.109 --> 21:17.545
Bartending exam. One.

21:17.578 --> 21:20.347
Name ingredients
in a Moscow Mule.

21:42.904 --> 21:44.939
Correct. Two.

21:44.972 --> 21:50.377
What is the proper glass in
which to serve a Bacardi Buck?

22:00.121 --> 22:01.364
How do you make sense
of the fact that

22:01.388 --> 22:06.093
you're working as a bartender?

22:27.515 --> 22:28.749
Designated driver?

22:28.783 --> 22:31.451
Designated Sherpa.

22:31.484 --> 22:32.887
Alison ForchÃ©.

22:32.920 --> 22:37.992
It's nice to meet you, Charles.

22:38.025 --> 22:41.796
With, um, with whom
are you on expedition?

22:41.829 --> 22:44.397
My brother Aiden is the drummer.

22:44.431 --> 22:48.069
Here, have a seat.

22:48.102 --> 22:50.571
We made a deal, I promised
that I would haul his gear

22:50.605 --> 22:52.740
around this weekend, if he
promises to haul my books

22:52.773 --> 22:54.675
across Manhattan in four months.

22:54.709 --> 22:56.443
What happens in four months?

22:56.476 --> 23:00.715
I'm graduating, moving, and then
I am starting my internship.

23:00.748 --> 23:02.617
Oh, wow, well, groovy.

23:02.650 --> 23:06.020
Have you thought about
my question?

23:06.053 --> 23:07.822
- Well...
- I'm sorry that I inundated you

23:07.855 --> 23:09.924
with all of these, it's just
that the groom's mother

23:09.957 --> 23:12.059
wanted me to toss them,
and I couldn't bear to.

23:12.093 --> 23:13.895
They're just so lovely.

23:13.928 --> 23:15.129
Alison! I need you!

23:15.162 --> 23:16.964
I'll be right there.

23:16.998 --> 23:18.065
I gotta go.

23:18.099 --> 23:19.867
Why get rid of them?

23:19.901 --> 23:21.002
The napkins?

23:21.035 --> 23:23.671
Oh, because of the typo.

23:23.704 --> 23:28.776
See? Li... live will
keep us together.

23:28.809 --> 23:32.213
Oh, is it a quote
from something?

23:32.246 --> 23:34.048
Okay.

23:34.081 --> 23:37.184
Not a big fan of popular music.

23:37.218 --> 23:39.452
Not really, no.

23:39.486 --> 23:41.689
Well, it's been fun.

23:41.722 --> 23:42.900
- Yeah.
- A promise is a promise.

23:42.924 --> 23:44.892
I should help my brother.

23:44.926 --> 23:46.036
I would like to see you again.

23:46.060 --> 23:48.195
I'll say goodbye before I leave.

23:48.229 --> 23:50.064
No, I meant like get a coffee...

23:50.097 --> 23:51.165
I know what you meant.

23:51.198 --> 23:53.634
I'm thinking about it.

23:53.668 --> 23:57.104
Plus, I fly to New York
tomorrow.

24:14.121 --> 24:16.257
Okay.

24:16.290 --> 24:23.898
I prefer written correspondence
to telephone conversations.

24:23.931 --> 24:28.636
And though you are under
no legal obligation

24:28.669 --> 24:32.506
to return this,
this is my favorite.

24:32.540 --> 24:35.743
So, use it, re-gift it.

24:35.776 --> 24:41.649
Whatever you do,
please do not throw it away.

24:58.833 --> 25:02.536
Goodbye, Charles.

25:06.574 --> 25:08.776
Before June 10th, I will be
at Columbia University.

25:08.809 --> 25:11.145
School of Law at this address.

25:11.178 --> 25:13.681
After June 10th when I graduate,
my law books and I

25:13.714 --> 25:16.083
will be living on West 10th,
at this address.

25:16.117 --> 25:18.652
It was a pleasure meeting you,
Charles.

25:18.686 --> 25:21.222
You are an excellent bartender.

25:21.255 --> 25:23.991
Nevertheless, I do hope that
you'll give some thought

25:24.025 --> 25:26.127
to that question.

25:26.160 --> 25:27.962
Best wishes, Alison.

25:27.995 --> 25:30.931
P.S. I'll want to have
children right away.

25:32.867 --> 25:34.035
May I help you?

